# System Design — Governed Biomedical GraphRAG Pipeline with Evidence Contracts

## Build

**Build 1 — Governed Biomedical GraphRAG Pipeline with Evidence Contracts**

Public title:

**Medical RAG Is Broken Without Evidence Contracts**

---

## 1. System purpose

This system answers safe biomedical evidence questions using public biomedical sources only.

The goal is not to build a medical chatbot.

The goal is to demonstrate how a biomedical AI system should be governed:

* normalize biomedical entities before retrieval
* retrieve evidence from public trusted sources
* combine vector retrieval with graph relationship lookup
* generate answers using retrieved evidence only
* validate claims against sources
* validate relationships against the graph
* block personal medical advice
* store an audit trail for every response

The LLM is not treated as the system of record.

The system of record is:

```text
retrieved evidence
graph relationships
evidence contracts
validation results
safety results
audit logs
```

---

## 2. High-level architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    User["User<br/>Safe biomedical evidence question"] --> UI["Streamlit Evidence Trace UI"]

    UI --> API["FastAPI Backend<br/>POST /query"]

    API --> Classifier["Query Classifier<br/>safe evidence question?<br/>medical advice?"]
    Classifier --> SafetyPrecheck["Safety Pre-Check"]

    SafetyPrecheck -->|Blocked personal advice| Refusal["Safe Refusal Response<br/>Redirect to public evidence summary"]
    SafetyPrecheck -->|Allowed evidence query| Extractor["Drug / Entity Extractor"]

    Extractor --> Normalizer["RxNorm Normalizer<br/>brand/generic/name mapping"]

    Normalizer --> Retriever["Hybrid Evidence Retriever"]

    Retriever --> DailyMed["DailyMed Retriever<br/>drug label sections"]
    Retriever --> PubMed["PubMed Retriever<br/>literature abstracts"]
    Retriever --> VectorStore["Vector Retriever<br/>semantic evidence chunks"]
    Retriever --> GraphDB["Neo4j Graph Retriever<br/>drug relationships"]

    DailyMed --> EvidenceBundle["Evidence Bundle Builder"]
    PubMed --> EvidenceBundle
    VectorStore --> EvidenceBundle
    GraphDB --> EvidenceBundle

    EvidenceBundle --> Generator["External LLM Generator<br/>structured answer only"]

    Generator --> EvidenceContract["Evidence Contract Builder<br/>claims + citations + graph paths"]

    EvidenceContract --> CitationValidator["Citation Validator"]
    CitationValidator --> ClaimValidator["Claim Validator"]
    ClaimValidator --> GraphValidator["Graph Consistency Validator"]
    GraphValidator --> SafetyFinal["Final Safety Checker"]

    SafetyFinal --> AuditLogger["Audit Logger<br/>query, evidence, claims,<br/>validation, safety, response"]

    AuditLogger --> Response["Structured Response<br/>answer + citations + validation + audit_id"]

    Response --> UI
```

---

## 3. Core design principle

The system should not trust generated text by default.

Every answer must pass through this governance path:

```text
question
  → classification
  → safety pre-check
  → entity normalization
  → evidence retrieval
  → graph lookup
  → answer generation
  → citation validation
  → claim validation
  → graph validation
  → final safety check
  → audit logging
  → response
```

If a claim cannot be validated, it should not be presented as a supported biomedical claim.

