## 14. Definition of done for the system

The system is complete enough for the first public demo when it can:

```text
1. Accept a safe biomedical evidence question.
2. Block personal medical advice questions.
3. Normalize at least the controlled MVP drug set.
4. Retrieve DailyMed evidence.
5. Retrieve PubMed evidence.
6. Build an evidence bundle.
7. Generate a structured answer.
8. Create claim-level evidence contracts.
9. Validate claims against retrieved sources.
10. Validate graph relationships.
11. Store an audit record.
12. Display the full evidence trace in Streamlit.
```

---

## 15. Final positioning

This build demonstrates biomedical AI infrastructure maturity.

The important point is not that an LLM can answer a drug question.

The important point is that the system can show:

```text
what it retrieved
what it normalized
what it claimed
what supported each claim
what graph path was used
what validation passed or failed
what safety boundary was enforced
what audit record was created
```

That is the difference between a generic RAG demo and a governed biomedical AI system.

